-- Sumitomo Mitsui to take $58.4 mln stake in India's Reliance Capital
-- By Aman Shah in Mumbai
-- Thu Dec 25, 2014 03:59AM EST
-- None



MUMBAI, Dec 25 (Reuters) - India's Reliance Capital Ltd <RLCP.NS> on Thursday said Japan's Sumitomo Mitsui Trust Bank will acquire an initial 2.77 percent stake in the company for $58.4 million.

Sumitomo Mitsui will buy the stake at 530 rupees per share through preferential allotment, Reliance Capital said in a statement. The deal represents a premium of 6.5 percent over the stock's Wednesday close.